Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice half the @shallot{1}(halved, peeled, and thinly sliced);
mince remaining shallot. Quarter @lemon{1}(quartered). Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}(halved).

In a #small bowl{}, combine sliced shallot, @sugar{1/4%tsp}, juice from half the lemon,
and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

== Burst Tomato Sauce ==

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{8%tsp} in a #small pot{} over medium heat. Add
tomatoes and minced shallot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tomatoes are
blistered, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Reduce to a low simmer and stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 1 TBSP water,
and as many @chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like. Cover and cook until thickened,
~{8-10%minutes}.

Remove pan from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}, smashing tomatoes slightly
with the back of a #spoon{}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Keep covered until ready to serve.

== Chicken Milanese ==

While sauce cooks, place @flour{1%tbsp} in a #shallow bowl{} and season with @salt{}.

In a second shallow bowl, whisk together @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} and 1 TBSP water.

Place @panko breadcrumbs{1/2%cup} in a third shallow bowl.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; place between two large
pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until chicken
is about 1⁄2 inch thick. Season all over with @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{},
and @pepper{}.

Working one piece at a time, coat chicken in seasoned flour. Gently shake off
excess, then dip into sour cream mixture until fully coated on both sides. Let
excess drip off, then press chicken into panko until fully coated.

TIP: For less mess, use #tongs{} to dip and transfer.

Heat a 1/3-inch layer of @cooking oil{} in a #large heavy-bottomed pan{} over
medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of flour sizzles immediately
when added to the pan, add coated chicken. Cook until golden brown and cooked
through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

TIP: Lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

Transfer to a #paper-towel-lined plate{}.

== Lemony Arugula Salad ==

Using a #slotted spoon{}, drain pickled shallot, reserving pickling liquid.

In a #large bowl{}, combine pickled shallot, @arugula{2%oz}, 2 TBSP olive oil,
and 2 tsp pickling liquid. Toss to thoroughly combine. Taste and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

TIP: Add more pickling liquid 1 tsp at a time for a tangier dressing.

== To Serve ==

Halve @burrata{4%oz}.

Divide chicken and salad between plates in separate sections. Add a pool of
sauce next to chicken and top with burrata.

Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.